author: Reuters Editorial
title: BRIEF-Westpac Banking Corp Says H1 Cash Earnings Rose 6 Pct
text:
May 7 (Reuters) - Westpac Banking Corp:
* H1 CASH RETURN ON EQUITY (ROE) 14.0% * H1 REPORTED NET INTEREST MARGIN INCREASED 11 BASIS POINTS TO 2.16%
* H1 NET INTEREST INCOME $8,301 MLN VS $7,693 MLN * “OUTLOOK FOR AUSTRALIA REMAINS POSITIVE WITH GDP GROWTH EXPECTED TO BE NEAR TREND AT AROUND 2.7% FOR REMAINDER OF 2018 AND 2019”
* “AUSTRALIAN HOUSING MARKET IS IN GOOD SHAPE” * “WESTPAC’S CREDIT PORTFOLIO IS FUNDAMENTALLY SOUND AND CONTINUES TO BE WELL POSITIONED”
* “HOUSEHOLD INCOME GROWTH REMAINS LACKLUSTRE AND INFLATION IS LOW. RESERVE BANK IS LIKELY TO KEEP RATES ON HOLD FOR SOME TIME”
* H1 OPERATING EXPENSES UP $50 MLN OR 1%, DUE TO REGULATORY AND COMPLIANCE COSTS INCLUDING ROYAL COMMISSION OF $34 MLN Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:
